, 0.00, 50, 0, NULL, '2026-07-30', '2026-07-31', '16:30:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '09:00:00', '16:30:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'events/tVdaIdyUg396pAFHVFbTGtvBRPSCoFdiRbjF48bZ.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'template_1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'c1c8e8e82642c9047d804013db492a52', 'events/qr/event-35-qr.png', '2026-06-10 04:59:22', '[]', '[]', NULL, 0, NULL, 0, '2026-06-10 04:59:22', '2026-06-10 04:59:30', '2026-06-10 04:59:30', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(36, 'Webinar Tips & Trik Penyusunan Proposal dan RAB Hibah Riset DPPM (Copy)', 'manage', 'Dr. Erna Hikmawati, S.Kom., M.Kom, Dr. Erna Hikmawati, S.Kom., M.Kom', '<p>Ingin proposal hibah riset Anda lebih kompetitif dan memiliki peluang lebih besar untuk lolos pendanaan? Bergabunglah dalam Webinar <i>Tips &amp; Trik Penyusunan Proposal dan RAB Hibah Riset DPPM</i> yang dirancang khusus untuk membantu dosen, peneliti, dan akademisi memahami strategi penyusunan proposal penelitian yang sesuai dengan kriteria penilaian DPPM.</p><p>Dalam webinar ini, peserta akan mendapatkan wawasan mengenai struktur proposal yang efektif, teknik merumuskan latar belakang dan metodologi penelitian, penyusunan luaran penelitian yang relevan, serta cara menyusun Rencana Anggaran Biaya (RAB) yang realistis, tepat sasaran, dan sesuai pedoman hibah. Selain itu, peserta juga akan mempelajari kesalahan-kesalahan umum yang sering menyebabkan proposal ditolak serta tips meningkatkan kualitas usulan penelitian.</p><p>Jangan lewatkan kesempatan untuk belajar langsung dari narasumber berpengalaman dan mempersiapkan proposal riset terbaik Anda menuju pendanaan hibah yang sukses.</p>', 'Kolaborasi antara BEST – Center of Excellence Sustainable Governance, AISINDO, dan IdSpora menghadirkan webinar eksklusif untuk membantu Anda memahami strategi penyusunan proposal dan RAB hibah riset DPPM secara tepat dan efektif.', 'DPPM', 'Webinar', '<ul><li>Peserta wajib melakukan pendaftaran melalui formulir yang telah disediakan oleh panitia.</li><li>Data yang diisikan saat pendaftaran harus benar, lengkap, dan dapat dipertanggungjawabkan.</li><li>Link akses webinar akan dikirimkan kepada peserta yang telah terdaftar melalui email atau media komunikasi yang ditentukan panitia.</li><li>Peserta diharapkan bergabung minimal 15 menit sebelum acara dimulai untuk memastikan kelancaran akses dan registrasi.</li><li>E-sertifikat akan diberikan kepada peserta yang memenuhi ketentuan kehadiran sesuai kebijakan panitia.</li><li>Peserta wajib menjaga etika dan sopan santun selama kegiatan berlangsung, baik dalam sesi presentasi maupun diskusi.</li><li>Dilarang menyebarkan link webinar kepada pihak yang tidak terdaftar tanpa izin dari panitia.</li><li>Materi yang disampaikan oleh narasumber merupakan hak kekayaan intelektual masing-masing narasumber dan tidak diperkenankan diperjualbelikan atau disebarluaskan tanpa izin.</li><li>Panitia berhak melakukan perubahan jadwal, susunan acara, atau narasumber apabila terdapat kondisi tertentu yang tidak dapat dihindari.</li><li>Dengan melakukan pendaftaran, peserta dianggap telah membaca, memahami, dan menyetujui seluruh syarat dan ketentuan yang berlaku.</li><li>Keputusan panitia terkait pelaksanaan webinar bersifat final dan tidak dapat diganggu gugat.</li></ul>', '\"Sertifikat Peserta|Materi|Contoh Proposal|Contoh RAB\"', 'Online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/1234567890?pwd=abc123XYZ789', 75000.00, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '2025-12-12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '09:00:00', '11:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'events/ymF8rScYwcxnqzk1EEdq0kP9K8o4pg0XiPI1ph4f.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'template_1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'e82cff1d9ea62f66432b7154cedf088d', 'events/qr/event-36-qr.png', '2026-06-10 04:59:52', '[{\"start\":\"08:30\",\"end\":\"09:00\",\"title\":\"Open Room Meet\",\"description\":\"Dipandu oleh panitia\"},{\"start\":\"09:00\",\"end\":\"09:10\",\"title\":\"Pembukaan + Pembacaan Doa\",\"description\":\"Dipandu Oleh MC\"},{\"start\":\"09:10\",\"end\":\"09:20\",\"title\":\"Sambutan\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"09:20\",\"end\":\"09:50\",\"title\":\"Materi\",\"description\":\"Oleh Pembicara\"},{\"start\":\"09:50\",\"end\":\"10:20\",\"title\":\"Materi\",\"description\":\"Oleh Pembicara\"},{\"start\":\"10:20\",\"end\":\"10:40\",\"title\":\"Sesi Tanya Jawab\",\"description\":\"Dipandu oleh MC\"},{\"start\":\"10:40\",\"end\":\"11:00\",\"title\":\"Penutupan + Dokumentasi\",\"description\":\"Dipandu oleh MC\"}]', '[]', NULL, 0, NULL, 0, '2026-06-10 04:59:51', '2026-06-10 04:59:52', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(37, 'lalala (Copy)', 'manage', 'Darren', '<p>tes</p>', 'tes', 'Programming', 'Workshop', NULL, NULL, 'Aula Lt.4 Fakultas Ilmu Terapan, Telkom University, Bandung', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/tMA4129ogGmrQLcF6', NULL, NULL, NULL, 20000.00, 0.00, NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-06-11', '2026-06-12', '12:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'events/CWMiAtDh3rehPBshUO1rZk9Rxseq7kSlgRpOekKq.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'template_1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'd390167621075c647012ffdebfcc036f', 'events/qr/event-37-qr.png', '2026-06-10 07:35:58', '[]', '[]', NULL, 0, NULL, 0, '2026-06-10 07:35:57', '2026-06-10 07:36:24', '2026-06-10 07:36:24', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(38, 'International Conference on Sustainable Impact Teaching and Learning through Pentahelix Collaboration (ICOSITL) - (IMPACT-EDU 2026)', 'manage', '', '<p>Scope: Research competition for lecturer with presentation in IMPACT-EDU Main Event. Authors must select ONE of the following four thematic pillars for their submission:&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>AI for Digital Learning Transformation</strong></li></ol><p>Focus on applications of artificial intelligence and machine learning in educational technology, digital learning environments, personalized learning paths, and innovative pedagogical approaches.</p><p><strong>2. Good Practices in Transnational Education</strong><br>Explore best practices in cross-border education, international collaboration, multicultural learning communities, and sustainable models for transnational higher education.</p><p><strong>3. OBE Consistency through Project-Based Learning</strong><br>Investigate how project-based learning methodologies ensure consistent alignment with Outcome-Based Education (OBE) principles and enhance student learning outcomes.</p><p><strong>4. End-to-End OBE Enabled by AI</strong><br>Examine how artificial intelligence can support the entire OBE framework—from curriculum design through assessment and outcome measurement—to improve educational effectiveness.</p><p><strong>Document Format</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Aspect</strong></td><td><strong>Requirement</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Paper Language</td><td>English</td></tr><tr><td>Paper Size</td><td>A4 (210 × 297 mm)</td></tr><tr><td>Orientation</td><td>Portrait</td></tr><tr><td>Page Length</td><td>Minimum 4 pages – Maximum 10 pages</td></tr><tr><td>Margin</td><td>Top, Bottom, Left, Right: 25 mm (1 inch)</td></tr><tr><td>Font Type</td><td>Times New Roman</td></tr><tr><td>Font Size (Body Text)</td><td>11 pt</td></tr><tr><td>Font Size (Headings)</td><td>12-14 pt (depending on level)</td></tr><tr><td>Spacing</td><td>1.15 line spacing (single spacing acceptable)</td></tr><tr><td>Text Alignment</td><td>Justified</td></tr><tr><td>Figures &amp; Tables</td><td>Embedded within the paper</td></tr><tr><td>File Format for Submission</td><td>Microsoft Word (.docx) or PDF</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Template &amp; Citation</strong></p><ul><li>Official ICOSITL 2026 template (<a href=\"https://tel-u.ac.id/icositl26-template\">https://tel-u.ac.id/icositl26-template</a>)</li><li>Citation style: IEEE Style. In-text citations use numbered square brackets [1], [2], etc. A numbered reference list must appear at the end of the paper in IEEE format.</li></ul><p><strong>Paper Structure</strong><br>Papers should follow this standard academic structure:<br><strong>1. Ttile</strong><br>Clear, concise, and descriptive of the research content.<br><strong>2.&nbsp; Author Name(s) and Affiliation(s)</strong><br>Include institutional affiliation and email contact information.<br><strong>3.&nbsp; Abstract</strong><br>150-250 words summarizing purpose, methods, key findings, and conclusions.<br><strong>4.&nbsp; Keywords</strong><br>4-6 keywords separated by commas, relevant to the paper\'s content.<br><strong>5.&nbsp; Introduction</strong><br>Present background, literature context, research gap, and research objectives.<br><strong>6.&nbsp; Methodology (or Literature Review)</strong><br>Describe research approach, methods, data sources, and analytical frameworks.<br><strong>7.&nbsp; Results/Findings</strong><br>Present research outcomes, data analysis, and major findings with supporting evidence (tables, figures).<br><strong>8.&nbsp; Discussion</strong><br>Interpret findings, compare with existing literature, discuss implications and limitations.<br><strong>9.&nbsp; Conclusion</strong><br>Summarize key findings, state contributions, and suggest directions for future research.<br><strong>10.&nbsp; References</strong><br>All cited sources formatted in IEEE Style. Should include recent publications (at least 50% of references from the last 5 years).</p><p><strong>Submission Process &amp; Review Procedure</strong><br><strong>Submission Steps</strong></p><ol><li>Download the official ICOSITL 2026 template</li><li>Prepare your paper following all guidelines&nbsp;</li><li>Submit via the online submission portal at&nbsp;</li><li>Monitor email for review status updates</li></ol><p><strong>Review Procedure - Two-Stage Process</strong><br><strong>Stage 1: Administrative Review (by Editorial Team)</strong></p><ul><li>Check format compliance with guidelines</li><li>Verify completeness of submission (all required sections present)</li><li>Ensure alignment with conference themes</li><li>Papers failing administrative review are returned for revision</li></ul><p><strong>Stage 2: Double-Blind Peer Review (by Independent Reviewers)</strong></p><ul><li>Papers passing administrative review enter peer review</li><li>Each paper is reviewed by TWO independent, anonymous reviewers</li><li>Author identity is hidden from reviewers (blind review)</li><li>Reviewers assess: originality, scientific rigor, clarity, relevance, and contribution</li><li>Review outcomes: ACCEPT, MINOR REVISIONS, MAJOR REVISIONS, or REJECT</li><li>Authors receive reviewer feedback and may be invited to revise</li></ul><p>ICOSITL 2026 is committed to fostering a rigorous, inclusive, and supportive environment for academic discourse on sustainable impact in teaching and learning. We welcome submissions that demonstrate original thinking, rigorous scholarship, and meaningful contributions to our thematic pillars. The double-blind peer review process ensures fair and objective evaluation of all submissions.<br>By submitting your paper, you acknowledge that you have read and understood all guidelines and requirements outlined in this document. For clarification on any aspect, please contact the editorial team as early as possible.</p><p>We look forward to receiving your high-quality submissions and seeing you at ICOSITL 2026!</p>', 'ICOSITL 2026 welcomes lecturers and researchers to submit original research papers for presentation, promoting excellence and innovation in teaching and learning with meaningful and sustainable impact.', 'Paper Competition', 'Lomba', '<h2><strong>Acceptance &amp; Publication Requirements</strong></h2><ol><li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong></li></ol><p>Papers are accepted for publication in the conference based on:</p><ul><li>Positive peer review evaluations from both reviewers</li><li>Successful revision (if revisions were requested)</li><li>Compliance with all format and guideline requirements</li><li>Paper presentation at the conference</li></ul><h2><strong>Ethics, Originality &amp; Copyright</strong></h2><ol><li><strong>Author Responsibilities</strong></li></ol><ul><li>Paper must be original work not previously published or submitted elsewhere</li><li>All authors must have contributed significantly to the research</li><li>Proper attribution and citations must be given to all sources</li><li>Research involving human subjects or sensitive data must comply with ethical guidelines</li><li>Authors must disclose any conflicts of interest or funding sources</li></ul><p><strong>2. Plagiarism Policy</strong><br>All submissions will be checked for plagiarism using standardized detection tools. Papers with plagiarism scores exceeding acceptable thresholds will be rejected without further review. Self-plagiarism (reuse of own previously published work) must be disclosed.</p><p><strong>3. Copyright &amp; Publication Rights</strong><br>By submitting to ICOSITL 2026, authors agree that their accepted paper may be published in the conference proceedings. Authors retain copyright to their work but grant the conference non-exclusive rights to publish and disseminate the paper. A copyright form will be required upon acceptance.</p>', '\"Certificate of Participation|Opportunity to Become a Top 20 Finalist Presenter|Access to IMPACT-EDU 2026 Sessions|Networking with National & International Participants|Coffee Break & Lunch (On-site Participants)|Deliver a 15 minute presentation at the Main Event IMPACT-EDU 2026\"', 'Damar Auditorium, Telkom University, Bandung, Indonesia', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/2FvLye1UmfLamvFUA', NULL, NULL, NULL, 750000.00, 750000.00, '2026-08-03 00:00:00', '2026-08-15 23:59:00', 0.00, 0.00, NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-09-09', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-11 00:00:00', '2026-07-10 23:59:00', '2026-07-30 08:00:00', '2026-09-04 23:59:00', '08:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'events/DqpY1tQ6F5G3CZvbBah2zxSGGoFbR9L8qd0JG9QX.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'template_1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{\"start\":\"2026-06-11\",\"end\":\"2026-07-10\",\"title\":\"Call for Submission\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-10\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Submission Deadline\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-13\",\"end\":\"2026-07-24\",\"title\":\"Review Process\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-30\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Announcement of Selection Results\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-08-03\",\"end\":\"2026-08-15\",\"title\":\"Finalist Registration\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-09-04\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Presentation Slide Submission Deadline\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-09-09\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Main Event & Finalist Presentation\",\"description\":\"\"}]', '[]', NULL, 1, '2026-06-16 01:51:02', 0, '2026-06-16 01:46:56', '2026-06-16 05:08:07', NULL, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(39, 'Teaching and Learning Innovation Showcase (For Lecturers and Education Support Staff) - IMPACT-EDU 2026', 'manage', '', '<p>Teaching &amp; Learning Innovation Showcase is a platform for lecturers and education support staff to showcase innovative teaching and learning practices that have been implemented or are currently being developed. As part of IMPACT-EDU 2026, this program promotes knowledge sharing, collaboration, and the advancement of impactful educational practices in higher education.</p><p>Participants are invited to submit an abstract describing their innovation in one of the following areas:</p><ul><li><strong>Outcome-Based Education (OBE)</strong>: OBE implementation, PLO/CLO design, learning outcome assessment, and Continuous Quality Improvement (CQI).</li><li><strong>AI in Learning</strong>: ethical use of Generative AI, adaptive learning, learning analytics, and personalized learning.</li><li><strong>Active Learning Innovation</strong>: flipped classroom, problem-based learning, project-based learning, gamification, and collaborative learning.</li><li><strong>Industry and Community Collaboration</strong>: integration of industry, government, community, and societal partners into learning and curriculum development.</li><li><strong>Digital, Numeracy, and AI Literacy</strong>: strengthening digital literacy, data literacy, numeracy, critical thinking, and responsible AI usage.</li><li><strong>LMS and Learning Technology</strong>: innovative use of LMS and digital technologies to support interactive, measurable, and meaningful learning experiences.</li></ul><p>All participants who successfully submit their work and complete the registration process will receive a Certificate of Participation. Submitted works will be reviewed by a panel of reviewers, and the Top 20 submissions will be selected as Finalists. Finalists will be invited to deliver a 15 minute presentation at the IMPACT-EDU 2026 Main Event on 9 September 2026 and will receive recognition as Top 20 Finalist Presenters. Selected finalists are required to complete a finalist registration process and submit their presentation slides by 4 September 2026 prior to the Main Event. One outstanding presenter will be awarded the IMPACT-EDU Innovation Award (Best Innovation).</p>', 'The Teaching & Learning Innovation Showcase gives lecturers and education staff a platform to share and present their innovative teaching practices, encouraging collaboration and inspiring ideas to drive meaningful impact in higher education.', 'Teaching & Learning Innovation', 'Lomba', '<ol><li>The program is open to lecturers and education support staff involved in teaching, learning, curriculum development, or academic support activities.</li><li>Participants must submit an abstract of their innovation through the designated submission link no later than 10 July 2026.</li><li>The Abstract Guidelines and Template are available at the following&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/16udMJf-TaztSyN0FOHLorPADU38NqjH5/edit?usp=sharing&amp;ouid=107381791834722998066&amp;rtpof=true&amp;sd=true\">link</a></li><li>All submissions will undergo a review and selection process conducted by the organizing committee and reviewers.</li><li>Participants who complete the submission and registration process are eligible to receive a Certificate of Participation.</li><li>The Top 20 submissions will be selected as Finalists and invited to present their work at the IMPACT-EDU 2026 Main Event.</li><li>Finalists are required to complete the finalist registration process within the specified registration period.</li><li>Finalists must submit their presentation materials (presentation slides) no later than 4 September 2026.</li><li>Each finalist will deliver a 15 minute presentation during the Main Event on 9 September 2026.</li><li>One outstanding presenter will be selected to receive the IMPACT-EDU Innovation Award (Best Innovation).</li><li>Registration fees are non-refundable.</li><li>The decisions of the reviewers and organizing committee are final and binding.</li></ol>', '\"Certificate of Participation|Opportunity to Become a Top 20 Finalist Presenter|Access to IMPACT-EDU 2026 Sessions|Networking with National & International Participants|Coffee Break & Lunch (On-site Participants)|Opportunity to Win the IMPACT-EDU Innovation Award\"', 'Damar Auditorium, Telkom University, Bandung, Indonesia', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/2FvLye1UmfLamvFUA', NULL, NULL, NULL, 500000.00, 500000.00, '2026-08-03 00:00:00', '2026-08-15 23:59:00', 0.00, 0.00, NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-09-09', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-11 00:00:00', '2026-07-10 23:59:00', '2026-07-30 08:00:00', '2026-09-04 23:59:00', '08:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'events/1kAxkG0bF5jRZllCH0pkemToAINSuS01Szw90VDm.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'template_1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{\"start\":\"2026-06-11\",\"end\":\"2026-07-10\",\"title\":\"Call for Submission\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-10\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Submission Deadline\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-13\",\"end\":\"2026-07-24\",\"title\":\"Review Process\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-30\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Announcement of Selection Results\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-08-03\",\"end\":\"2026-08-15\",\"title\":\"Finalist Registration\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-09-04\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Presentation Slide Submission Deadline\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-09-09\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Main Event & Finalist Presentation\",\"description\":\"\"}]', '[]', NULL, 1, '2026-06-16 03:00:50', 0, '2026-06-16 02:35:46', '2026-06-16 05:08:24', NULL, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(40, 'Student Learning Innovation Poster Competition - IMPACT-EDU 2026', 'manage', '', '<p>The Student Learning Innovation Poster Competition is open to active Diploma (D3/D4), Bachelor\'s (S1), and Master\'s (S2) students. Participation may be individual or team-based, consisting of 2–5 students with one poster submission per team.<br>This competition focuses on ideas, experiences, best practices, reflections, solutions, products, prototypes, and learning outcomes that contribute to improving the quality of teaching and learning in higher education. Submissions should demonstrate students’ active engagement in creating learning experiences that are relevant, collaborative, technology-enhanced, and impactful for both academic communities and society.</p><p><strong>Topics include:</strong></p><ul><li>Student Experience in Outcome-Based Education (OBE)</li><li>Ethical Use of AI for Student Learning</li><li>Active Learning from Student Perspective</li><li>Industry and Community-Based Student Projects</li><li>Digital Literacy, Numeracy, and AI Literacy for Students</li><li>Meaningful Use of LMS and Learning Technology</li><li>Student Innovation for Sustainable Learning Impact</li></ul><p><strong>Poster requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>A1 size (594 × 841 mm)</li><li>Portrait orientation</li><li>High-resolution PDF or JPG (minimum 300 dpi)</li><li>English language</li></ul><p>All participants who successfully submit their poster and complete the registration process will receive a Certificate of Participation. All submissions will undergo a review process, and the Top 20 posters will be selected as Poster Finalists.<br>Selected Poster Finalists will be invited to showcase their posters during the IMPACT-EDU 2026 Main Event through a dedicated Poster Exhibition. Each finalist team is required to assign at least one representative to attend the event and be present at the poster booth to engage with visitors, answer questions, and explain their work throughout the exhibition session.<br>One outstanding poster will be selected to receive the Best Poster Award, consisting of a certificate and a cash prize.</p>', 'The Student Learning Innovation Poster Competition offers students a platform to display creative ideas and solutions that improve higher education quality, sharing their work with academics and practitioners from various institutions worldwide.', 'Poster Competition', 'Lomba', '<ol><li>The competition is open to active D3/D4, Bachelor\'s (S1), and Master\'s (S2) students.</li><li>Participation may be individual or team-based, consisting of 2–5 students.</li><li>Each participant/team may submit only one poster.</li><li>Posters must be prepared in English and follow the specified format: A1 size (594 × 841 mm), portrait orientation, PDF or JPG format, minimum 300 dpi resolution.</li><li>Poster files must be submitted through the designated submission link no later than 10 July 2026.</li><li>The Poster Guidelines available at the following&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qsupWMUJam8C6wQ0aVki_xQOIOGCiiaUJteP-soKj9s/edit?usp=sharing\">link</a>&nbsp;</li><li>All submissions will undergo a review and selection process conducted by the reviewers.</li><li>Participants who complete the registration and submission process are eligible to receive a Certificate of Participation.</li><li>Twenty selected posters will be designated as Poster Finalists and invited to participate in the Poster Exhibition at the IMPACT-EDU 2026 Main Event.</li><li>Finalists are required to complete the finalist registration process within the specified registration period.</li><li>Each finalist team must appoint at least one representative to attend the Main Event and be present during the Poster Exhibition session.</li><li>One outstanding poster will receive the Best Poster Award (Certificate and Cash Prize).</li><li>Registration fees are non-refundable.</li><li>The decisions of the reviewers and organizing committee are final and binding.</li></ol>', '\"Certificate of Participation|Opportunity to Become a Top 20 Poster Finalist|Poster Exhibition at IMPACT-EDU 2026|Networking with National & International Participants|Coffee Break & Lunch (One On-site Representative per Finalist Team)|Opportunity to Win the Best Poster Award\"', 'Damar Auditorium, Telkom University, Bandung, Indonesia', 'https://maps.app.goo.gl/2FvLye1UmfLamvFUA', NULL, NULL, NULL, 350000.00, 350000.00, '2026-08-03 00:00:00', '2026-08-15 23:59:00', 0.00, 0.00, NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-09-09', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-11 00:00:00', '2026-07-10 23:59:00', '2026-07-30 08:00:00', '2026-08-15 23:59:00', '08:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'events/EH7LeE2D4afshQt5WhpYH3QM9FPbgfxxMBMntkWr.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'template_1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{\"start\":\"2026-06-11\",\"end\":\"2026-07-10\",\"title\":\"Call for Submission\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-10\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Submission Deadline\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-13\",\"end\":\"2026-07-24\",\"title\":\"Review Process\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-07-30\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Announcement of Selection Results\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-08-03\",\"end\":\"2026-08-15\",\"title\":\"Finalist Registration\",\"description\":\"\"},{\"start\":\"2026-09-09\",\"end\":\"\",\"title\":\"Poster Exhibition at IMPACT-EDU 2026\",\"description\":\"\"}]', '[]', NULL, 1, '2026-06-16 03:02:12', 0, '2026-06-16 02:59:39', '2026-06-16 05:09:18', NULL, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL);
